cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses different types of phishing attacks and anti-phishing techniques to mitigate them. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of mobile devices in daily life and how people can be made aware of phishing attacks and how to avoid them. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper discusses the development of anti-phishing techniques and their assessment. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also possible as the paper discusses the impact of phishing attacks on individuals and society. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of mobile devices for communication and how phishing attacks can exploit social networks.
